There is a bug when you click on the "Show issue navigator for #" link under a version on the planning board, it takes you to the advanced search as expected but has two sort fields in the query. For instance:

{code}project = 10000 AND fixVersion = 10000 AND status = "3" AND status in ("1", "4") ORDER BY key ASC, key ASC{code}

Note the "ORDER BY key ASC_, key ASC_" which gives a JQL error.

I was thinking last night that there may be a problem with your Quartz job. A customer upgrading to 4.0 will have this happen to them:

# Start JIRA.
# JIRA will see the {{GreenHopperIndexes}} job but will not be able to construct it since the {{GreenHopperRankingJob.class}} it lives inside of the GH plugin.
# JIRA will then still create the GreenHopperIndexes job but will insert the {{NoOpJob.class}}.
# At GH startup, you will look for the GreenHopperIndexes job and will find it. However, the JOB will actually be doing nothing.

The overall result, your job is not going to being registered. If this is the case then you will have to do some extra checks in your registration code. I guess you can check that the job is registered and has the right class. For example, 

{code}
   job = ManagerFactory.getScheduler().getJobDetail(....) 
   if (job != null && job.getGetJobClass() != GreenHopperRankingJob.class)
   {
       <unregister the current job>
       job = null;
     }
   if (job = null)
   {
       <register the current job>
   }
{code}

It may be worth while to look if the job is non-volatile and always remove it to clean up the database.

We are getting these messages in JAC that are incorrectly reporting they are coming from the {{AbstractSingleFieldType}}. Can you please create your own logger to log this message under to make it easier to track down this message in the future. It was a mistake on our behalf to make the logger available to fields.

{code}
2009-08-28 03:25:44,621 http-j2ee.jira.atlassian.com%2F127.0.0.101-8080-Processor114 WARN anonymous 12291x135x103 b1134o http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-8841 [issue.customfields.impl.AbstractSingleFieldType] Repairing ranking for [JRA-18268]
{code}

